==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cowpox
<hw>Cow"pox`</hw> <pr>(-p⟦ocr⟧ks`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A pustular eruptive disease of the cow, which, when communicated to
the human system, as by vaccination, protects from the smallpox;
vaccinia; -- called also <altname>kinepox</altname>,
<altname>cowpock</altname>, and <altname>kinepock</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cowquake</ent>⟦br⟧
